			<description><![CDATA[<p>
You&#39;ll manage the product development cycle and be responsible for making our product and user experience insanely great. This will require a passion for interaction design and product management.</p>
<div class="section">
<p>
We care deeply about human interfaces that are so good, they are invisible - so should you!</p>
<p>
<u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>
</div>
<div class="section">
<ul>
<li>
Manage the product release cycle.</li>
<li>
Continually improve how users interact with our software.</li>
<li>
Take ownership of supporting collateral to improve the on-boarding process (i.e the sign up flow).</li>
<li>
Understand the market and be aware of our competition.</li>
<li>
Manage external resources, such as usability testers.</li>
<li>
To have an eye for detail, and understand that less is often more.</li>
<li>
Work with visual design talent to ensure our app looks fantastic.</li>
<li>
To always err on the side of simplicity and make sure this translates to our products.</li>
<li>
Understand user journeys, funnels, visitor metrics and how to analyse this data to improve the product.</li>
<li>
Know when to say no!</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section">
<p>
<u><strong>You Must:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Have experience in bringing a product to market. This could be from a previous job, or your own side project. We&#39;re keen to learn how you approached the problem.</li>
<li>
Provide examples of occasions where you improved a user experience, and explain your choices.</li>
<li>
Be able to simplify complex ideas and methodologies: the simplification process is at the core of our product.</li>
<li>
Be passionate about startup culture - if you expect a 9-to-5, stop reading now.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section">
<p>
<u><strong>In A Typical Day You:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Initiated some user testing of an upcoming release.</li>
<li>
Setup milestones for the next major version and kickstarted development.</li>
<li>
Wireframed some ideas for how we can simplify the signup process and discussed these with the team.</li>
<li>
Setup a trial of a new project management tool you think might be useful.</li>
<li>
Wrote a blog post detailing the highlights of our latest version.</li>
<li>
Helped storyboard a video to showcase our app - we think it will improve conversions.</li>
<li>
Looked at the results of recent user testing and discussed with the team how to address the issues raised.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section">
<p>
<u><strong>Bonus Points For:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Having experience in, or an understanding of, the insurance/finance industry.</li>
<li>
Having experience with B2B applications.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section">
